If you don't want to use the `open` package, you can use the built-in `vscode.env.openExternal` method to open a URL in the user’s default web browser.

Here’s how you can write your `extension.ts`:

```typescript
import * as vscode from 'vscode';

export function activate(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {
  let disposable = vscode.commands.registerCommand('googleInVscode.openGoogle', () => {
    // Use the vscode.env.openExternal method to open the default web browser
    vscode.env.openExternal(vscode.Uri.parse('https://www.google.com')).catch((err) => {
      vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Failed to open Google: ${err}`);
    });
  });

  context.subscriptions.push(disposable);
}

export function deactivate() {}
```

